CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 17, 1954, pg. 11, reads: "Smith-Gaines Newlyweds - Marsha Guerelan Smith, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Carl S. Carter, married John A. Gaines, July 3, with the Rev. J.A. Williams, pastor of Baptist Temple Church, officiating. A reception followed in church social rooms.  Among the many guests was the grandmother of the bride, Mrs. Irene F. Carter, of Washington, D.C. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of groom John A. Gaines and bride Marsha Guerelan Smith Gaines wearing gown with full skirt, lace sleeves, and sheer floral yoke, holding sprigs of lily of the valley with bow, posed in domestic interior with floral curtains
